      "message": "\u003e It\u0027s only set in the parent process, in the child it picks up value from the parent environment and uses that.\n\nRIght. I mean that if this were\n\n  ScopedEnvironmentVariable(const wchar_t* name, const wchar_t* new_value)\n\nit’d be easier to use, since the only time you ever construct one of these, you immediately set a new value.",
