      "writtenOn": "2017-03-24T15:54:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Did you LOG instead of PLOG to catch the other non-GetLastError()-setting things that WaitForSingleObject() might return? I think we can assume that if it’s not WAIT_OBJECT_0, it was WAIT_FAILED, and just PLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"WaitForSingleObject\" here.",
      "revId": "0a00c425eee03417b85cc256ed3b89dcfe90c8e3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4e186a92_a992bf81",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_win_test.cc",
