        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-24T17:59:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Logging both for belt-and-suspenders. err might be significant if ever it\u0027s not WAIT_FAILED.\n\nOK, I like your style! And it’s good to share the extra bits that we get from GetLastError() via PLOG(). But err isn’t WAIT_FAILED, then GetLastError() is irrelevant and confusing, so I think:\n\n  if (err \u003d\u003d WAIT_FAILED) {\n    PLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"WaitForSingleObject\";\n  } else if (err !\u003d WAIT_OBJECT_0) {\n    LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"WaitForSingleObject returned \" \u003c\u003c err;\n  }",
      "parentUuid": "4e186a92_a992bf81",
      "revId": "0a00c425eee03417b85cc256ed3b89dcfe90c8e3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
